tics, Genetic Nature/Culture is a model of fruitful dialogue, presenting the quandaries faced by scholars on both sides of the two-cultures debate.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aAnthropological ethicsvCongresses. 0aAnthropology. 0aBioethics. 0aHuman geneticsxMoral and ethical aspectsvCongresses. 0aHuman geneticsxResearchvCongresses. 0aHuman population geneticsvCongresses. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / General.2bisacsh  aacademic.  aafrican american.  aamazonia.  aamazons.  aancient world.  aanthropologist.  aanthropology.  acloning.  acritique.  acultural anthropology.  acultural divide.  acultural history.  acultural studies.  aculture.  adiscourse.  adna.  adolly the sheep.  aessay anthology.  aessay collection.  aeugenics.  agenes.  agenetics.  ahealth sector.  ahealthcare.  ahuman evolution.  ahuman genome.  aindigenous people.  anatural world.  anature.  ascholarly.  avirtual reality.1 aDuster, Troy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEscobar, Arturo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFranklin, Sarah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFujimura, Joan H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoodman, Alan H., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGoodman, Alan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaraway, Donna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeath, Deborah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeath, Deborah, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHeller, Chaia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKaestle, Frederika A., ec